Tindal se to sayad hi koi jaanta hoga tujhe but singh se to tu poore campus me famous tha wo senior ho yaa koi junior bas singh bolna hai samajh aa jaani thi ki baat kiski ho rahi ü§©
Bhai itna jyada hai tere baare me ki kaha se shuru karu kaha khatam karu kuch pta nahi chal rha bs Zindagi bhar ke liye jo nishaan tune diya hai wo har din dekh ke yaad aayegi teri ü§ï üòÇ 
Ek akela bhai jiske saath meri jamne lagi thi reason btane ki jarurat nahi haiüö≠ Bhai shuru se last tak bina tere room gaye hue maja hi nahi aata tha aur wo alag baat hai 10 me se 2 baari tu room pe milta tha.Bhai tere karan mai kitne logo se mil paaya aur saare tere dost dost nhi bhai jaise lagte theü§©ü§© . Bhai kitne tripod ka hissa hain humlog tumhe ache se yaad hoga. Kya mast rahti thi apni aaj bahar jaana hai to jaana hai kah kar wo chaahe endsem ki night ho yaa normal night ho mast Nightout maar ke aate the aur wo Nightout nahi memories hai jo mai college ke baad sayad kabhi na kar paaun waisa kyunki tumlog ke jaisa milna mushkil hi nahi naamumkin hai üòç. And I am lucky to have you in my life broü§©üòç
Aur meri gpl ke time tu eklauta tha jiske laat se mujhe sabse jyada dar aata rahi thi aur mai pahle to khush tha ki tu available nahi hai but fr aate hi Jo kohraam machaya tune wo poora ka poora time rewind ho rha mere aankho ke saamne kaise mere saamne naach kar laat chla rahe the üò§ Lucky tu bhi maan apne aap ko ki mai tere koi bhi birthday pe nahi tha gpl ke timeüòÑ But rahta bhi to raham kar deta kyunki humesha mareej jo ban jaata tha tu. Tere alawa sayad hi hoga koi insaan campus me jo start ke har college fest me bimaar pad ke hospital me admit hota tha aur uske karan hume bhi rahna padta thaüòÑ aur tera fever ka kyahi kahna üôÑ
Aur sayad wahi wajah thi ki itne jyada log tujhpe girte the aur tinder match ka to koi comparison hi nahi haiüòÑ
Bhai jaldi hi milte hain bhai yaha kyahi aur kitna hi likhi sab kam hai tere liye to. Bas jaldi milke ek trip karte hain bakchod wala jisme sabhi wapas se mile aur haan yaad karna band mat karna mujhe nahi to Hyderabad se Bangalore aate hue der nahi lagegi mujhe üòúüòÅ

text: Be bhoshdike bete yaad aa jaani chahiye saari baat agar mai bas memories ka naam lu to tere se itna to expect kar hi sakta hu jitna tu close ho gya hai mere aur pta hi hai aalsi bhi utna hi hu to bahut kam likhunga bt samjh jaana bas jo chutiyaapa failaaya hai tune use sahi kar. Ik ki tune try maara but ho nahi paaya. Mai to ab bas Kaash ban ke rah gya ki Kaash mai wha hota to aisa nahi hone deta but sach bataun to mai dar ke nahi aana chaha udhar kyunki mai bahut bada daldal me phansh jaata kyunki dono hi taraf mere jigri dost the aur mai agar wha hota to beech me pis jaata aur poora happiness barbaad ho jaata tabhi maine decide kiya tha ki naa jaau aur to aur bahana bhi mil gya tha paiso wala aur kismat bhi thori saath de di ki wha se nikla to alag alag trip bhi ban gaye dosto ke sath to mai to naahi to regret kar sakta naahi blame kar sakta bas last ki jo kch memories banani thi clg me usme saath nahi de paaya baaki tujhe bhi pta hai ki kon sa aisa din nahi rha tha clg me jisme apan log ne masti ya bakchodi naa kari ho. Aur mujhe aaj bhi yaad hai pahli baar sabse achi bonding tujhse hi hui thi aur fr aaj tak wo kabhi tooti nahi balki alag alag memories hi create karte rahe kitno ko yaad Karu tinder se leke summer room partner se leke ye placement (yaha thori shikayat thi) but fr usse nikal ke wo achanak se fr se milna kanpur Central pe aur kahte hain na achi bonding jaha ho jaati hai wha plan nahi karni padti plan khud humare liye work karti hai aur fr wha bhi 1 month ke upar rahe wha start me to masti kari humlogo ne bt baad me tune mood ki maa bahan karna start kari tumne bt fr sambhaal hi liya tha samajh aur fr se wahi masti kayam rahi apni. Aur haan placement ki shikayat ye hai ki tune jab se placement ki preparation se leke placement lag jaane tak to full confidence dilata rha aur sach batau to thora dar se bhi padh liya karta tha ki ye cse ka hai to kch bhi puch sakta hai to start jab coding se kari thi to achi chal rahi thi and ki bhi achi mehnat thi hum teeno ne but jab meri hui thi aur tujhe btaya tha to ik Teri nahi lagi thi us time bt meri khushi me tu khush to nahi tha bas ye shikayat rahi tujhse üò°. But jaise hi hui teri mujhe yaad hai tune tab jaake ache se congratulations bola tha mjhe ü§©ü§©. So thanks for all memories which we have created ü§ó wo chaahe cricket se leke bandi tak ki ho sab me aise jagah pe partner tu hi tha aur bas tu aage miliyo to pahle waale Mohit mc se milu aisa feel karwana nahi to udhar hi is baar band bahana start karunga teri üòä. Baaki safe rah aur yaad karte rahna mai naa karu fir bhi kyunki mai thora bhulakkad hu ye pta to chal hi gya hoga üòÇ Aur agar koi bhi baat buri lagi ho to lawda farak nahi padta mujhe aur sunaunga hi tujhe agar inme se kisi baat ke liye rr kiya toü§¨üòÑ.

text:
Bhai, 
Saalon se jaanta hu terko. Pehle jitta energetic, annoying, irritating aur kanjoos tha, abhi bhi hai. But usse kahi zyada important, pehle jitta friendly, honest, caring aur humble tha utta aaj bhi hai. Mei bohot regret krta hu beech mei tujhse baat na krna but college mei shukar hai tune mujhe maaf kr diya. Different halls mei hone ke baad bhi apan almost roz milte the. Tere saath almost saare fests dekhe hai, raat - raat ko assignments kiye hai, profs ki bitching ki hai, GOT subah jag ke dekha hai, courses ki tension ki hai,  grades ke liye roya hai, placements ki tension ki hai, yeh moments kabhi nhi bhulunga. Although, woh iRage wale ka code tujhe merko bta dena chahiye tha :P, but fir bhi you are really special in my life.  Ab itte saalon ke baad apan alag cities mei honge, hopefully iss baar contact mei rahenge. Hamesha aisa hi rhiyo bro, never change and live your life to the fullest. 
All the best.
author: Anirudh  Garg

text:
Heyy Jaya,
We met for the first time when we had the interview for the Summer project at Electronics Club in summer '18. I remember you literally knowing everything about Skin Track, and I not know anything about it, but somehow I got through, and we got placed in the same team. That summer was fun: soldering circuits, building electrodes, checking 80 MHz oscillators, learning to code ESP8266, and then subsequently coding it a million times over and dealing with the male and female headers :P, and of course, dealing with our arrogant team leader (I hope you remember :P). To be honest, you were the most motivated among all of us to do the project, and it is because of you only that it ever got completed. In hindsight, that was the project that got me the internship eventually, so I guess I have a lot to be thankful to be you. You are literally the most helpful person I know and, above all a special friend. Thank you for overlooking the times when I have been indifferent to you, and thank you for always cracking me up with your pronunciation of Github :P and also choosing Cult meet over Tech meet in winter '18 :D. Always stay the same, never change, and stop pulling my leg so often :P. Wish we stay connected in the future.
All the best.

text:
O ma Bebo :-*
Sabse mast aadmi of my college life. Jiske saath masti bhi bahut ki aur seekha bhi bahut kuch. 
First Impression: Big Guy from Odisha, probably killed a few people before, who goes to canteen A LOT.
Can't forget tera Philosphy padhana mujhe xD. Second year me tujhe roommate banae ke liye almost lad hi liya tha mein. And I am glad. Tere saath din-raat gossips, ghar ki stories, aur mazaks sabme bahut maze aate the. You are probably one of the very very few people who have seen me cry in college. You have been someone jisse sab khulke share kiya hai meine. Tere se life ke baare me bahut seekha mein. Tujhe shayad na pata ho but tere random gyans have helped me a lot to grow up. 
Tere saath PUBG khelna (Ping968 <3) was/is so much fun. Esp bcoz you are a pro gamer. Be it cards or any shooting game.
Can't forget that day jab teri lab miss ho gayi thi. üòÇ
You will definitely go places, bro. You are one of the most hardworking and dedicated (not to mention brilliant) guy I know. 
For me, you would always be the big burly guy who is very mature of his age and pure by heart.

text:
Hi Umang!
I can never thank you enough for being there. You have always been my go-to guy. Koi bhi problem ho ya kuch suggestion chahiye ho mujhe humesha I know I can reliably turn towards you. Your work ethics have always inspired me. Kaafi chill wala banda hai tu, and bahut hi rare instances me kabhi gussa hua hai.
Wing ka Tech God rha hai tu humesha se. Laptop se lekar mouse lene take sab tere se aake pucha hai meine.
I am happy that we got to share so many memories together. Antaragni PR (paise wapas nhi kiye unhone :p) me saath me kaam kiya tha sabse pehle. Kaafi fun times the wo. Also first year me wing ke saath EDM jaana. Oh and your Euphoria wala dance üòç
Odessey Treasure Hunt, Takneek aur SnT code me kya hi maze kiye hain bhai. Saath me questions solve krne ka try karna.... kitne mazedar moments the wo.
DSA ke question se lekar Valorant tak har jagah you have been the one carrying me.
One thing that I am super proud of you about was your SCD profile. Although deleted, original copy mere pass abhi bhi padi hui hai :p
And that one time you commented on a YT channel (thanks for that, I was secretly happy for that :p)
You have been one of those guys who was always up for group video calls. Those late-night video calls and discussion sessions are some of the most cherishable memories. 
You were an integral part of my placement journey bro. From the silliest doubts to the most challenging problems you were always there to guide me. 
Our PUBG and Valorant sessions have been legendary. Ping968 ka Miramar match kabhi nhi bhul sakta hu.

First-year me star gazing to third-year me next-door-roomie, it has been a truly amazing bonding, at least for me. From canteen trips to mess trips, from discussing politics to life experiences, from participating in treasure hunts to pubg rank push, from waking up for breakfast to late-night skribble games, it has been really fun times.

text: To chaliye milate hai tumhe apni chapu dost Jaya se jo whatsapp DP tak lgane m dimaag lgati hai....CC m ghanto bitane waali jaya ki bakchodi wali personality, kam hi log dekh paaye, I was one of those luckey persons. This rivelry started from second year and of course will contiue forever... but let me recall those last few years... we got to know each other after our first long talk in CC, again jahan ham dono apna apna rr kiye the, isme ham dono hmesha ek doosre se compete karte, kyuki kahin aur tumse compete karne ki meri aukaat nahi hai....I got a chance a to look at the human inside you after my favourite treat of momos given by you, kya hi thi wo raat, we almost became business partners on that day bas business abhi tak nahi khul paaya apna, I hope aage khul paayega. But that business idea was as unique as this friendship is: "ek dukhi insaan ko doosre jyada dukhi insaan se milwana". We both inspired each other ki fraud kaise maarna hota hai, whether it was a project under Himanshu sir, or was it a course under arnab. Khair padhai likhai se door chalte hai kyuki yahan tum ulta mujhe inspire karti ho, aur bakchodi par wapas aate hai, I remember that unique exam of all the tharki boys you took in chemical freshers "Jisme hme 20 30 ladkiyon k naam btane the from our batch" and we all failed in that. We both shared the same interests whether it was a trip plan to Goa (Jo wahan hoga, wo wahin rah jaayega) or it was a boring subject of mass transfer (of course I still have that sketch made by you in mass transfer class). Things always got spicy between us whenever we used to plan someone's marriage on OAT rooftop or discuss someone's breakup in NCL or in long night walks. I'm blessed to have a friend like you jo hmesha mere khane ka payment kar deta, you were the reason I got a chance to visit GH's canteen, wrna m kahan himmat kar pata GH m ghusne ki. Even though it's been a while since I met yoo last time but never felt that you're ever going away from me, this friendship is still as strong as it was ever(though tera phone abhi tak thik nahi hua).....Yar ek trip se kya hoga, mujhe jyada karne hai but pata nahi kab tum ghar se nikalogi, m to hmesha taiyar hoo tere saath bhagne ko but it seems mujhe hi aana padega tujhe tere ghar se kidnap karne....I wanted to roam around again in those lonely streets of campus but I missed that chance.... I miss you buddy... I hope this wait will be over soon and I will get a chance to discuss another dukh bhari khani of someone with you on a "treat by you". I'll always be there for any sort of bakchodi with you just never forget to ping me once....
author: Kuldeep  Singh

text: Bhai ab to btade campus m kon pasand hai...I can't remember a single moment jab ham ek doosre ko dekhkar na hase ho, bc itni bhi joker jaisi sakal nahi hai, par hasi to aa hi jaati, I was never in even a percent of you but always tried to catch up to you, Bhai tu hai chapu maan le, Bahut RR machata hai, fir hmi ko chhorkar aage badh jaata hai, ham ussi bakchodi m fase rah jaate, Lucknow shaandar tha but usse bhi shaandaar wo raat, How can I forget our "Aishwrya rai" dancing on "Kajra re" and then that stud guy dancing in hall 8 on the ocassion of diwali, sab log bas group m circle bnakar tujhe hi taad rahe the. I always figured a part of me in you, I never missed a chance to brag about you infront of people. Dhyaan se dekhiye iss masoom se chehre k peeche chipe stud launde ko, jispar ladkiyaan marti hai, but bhai sahab bhaav nahi dete, Bhai Badminton m jo maarta tha tu hmesha yaad rahega. You have been one of my close friend since 1st year and I'm glad that I made a friend like you.I'm happy that you transform yourself with a better version of yours after 2nd year Udgosh, I wish I could have done the same. Honestly speaking I feel a bit jealous at that time that I could not able to spent more time with you and I guess I've told you this before also. One more thing that really found irritate when we go to any shop is that you are very very very particular about the thing you buy. That's good in a way, but still it's a bit annoying. But your taste and choice in any thing like food, sweets, gifts, decor etc. all are too good. That's why I ask you first before buying anything. There are a lot of things where you struggled and came with improvement. There are very few people around whom I feel comfortable in campus and you know you are first one of them. There are a lots of flashback are coming to my mind right now, I don't know how to put those things in words. I just hope we could again have fun as before in campus. I hope 17th March 2020 will not be the last time of our togetherness. Hope to see you soon. Stay safe...Take care

text:
Yooooooooooo Beta Tester!!
Bahot chaapu ho bhai tum. Damn man, it was one heck of a journey that we had together. There were lows, highs, HIGHs and what not. From spending the darkest semester together to having fun together in the last one month at iitk it was a very nimce journey - a really special one. I will never forget that journey. Thank you for being there throughout the journey, thanks for being there when I needed someone. Damn I remember we started bonding by being project partner in CSE courses and damn we did a lot of course assignments, projects together. Thanks for covering up for me when I was not contributing well in some of the projects. All the best for your future bro. I know it is going to be awesome and you are going to achieve great things kyunki tum utne chapu ho and you will do it, for sure!! Love you man!!
 Also, trips plan karte hai jald hi!!

text:
Madarchod Shubhankar
KYa be bsdk mere maze lene mein bahut maza aata hai , gaand maar doonga khade khade. Waise to hum football ground mein mile the tu achha khelta tha I admit it lekin tera tatti headers ab bhi yaad karta hoon to hansi aa jaati hai.
Tere ko IFL team mein naa leke sabse mast kaam kiya tha maine nahi to sala final bhi nahi khel paate.
Waise jitna bura to banne ki koshish karta hai uska ek percent bhi nahi hai, mere height ko lekar tera same se joke sun ke bore ho gaya tha.
bahut saari parties ki hain saath mein, bahut maza aaya yaar , tu nahi hota to football khelna boring ho jata mere liye.
Tera food choice bahut mast hai harr baar maza aa jata tha jab bhi tu order karta tha .Main wo lucknow ki trip pe nahi jaa paya uska dukh hai mujhe, khair chhodo.
Tu jo bhi life mein accomplish karna chaah raha hai wo jarror milega tujhe aakhir mera putra hai naa tu.
Bsdk jab bhi mere pangaa lega maa chod doonga teri.
 P.S.- AAnd ka naa gaand ka gyaan chode bramhaand kaa. ye tu hi

Peace out lekin apna war to chalta hi rahega , khus raho bsdk.

 Tumara Madarchod Mitra

Priya Bhrata Suraj
Jab bhi tumhe yaad karta hoon to ek hansta hua chehra yaad aata hai. Teri prem kahaani sun ke mujhe ek baat to pakki hai ki struggler aadmi hai, aage bhi jeevan main kabhi haar mat maana struggle karte rahna. Last ke do mahine mein bahut maze aaye , tere kahne pe gaanga foonka hoon. Ek slaah dena chahoonga, (iss salaah ko kisi puraane incident se mat jodga ye in general) maafi maangne se kabhi koi chhota nahi hota, baat sahi galat to baad ki baat hai lekin agar saamne waale ka dil saaf ho to uska dil rkhne ke liye bhi sorry bola jaa sakta hai.
Bahut ho gayi serious baat, tune hamare pariwaar ka naam roshan kiya baapu ko bahu dilaayi aur wo bhi hame maar khilaaye bina unlike Jaspreet.

P.S.-Keep smiling aur Neha ka saath mat chhodna , mujhe prem kahaniyaan anjaam tak pahunte dekhne mein achha mahsoos hota hai.

author: Aviral  Shukla

text:
Jab bhi humari baat hogi to Sainik School sabse pehle aayega. Jo bond 2 Sainik school vaalon ke beech me ho sakta hai vo normally nahi hota. Starting from the PHY101 lab jahan hum lab partners the, baaki log values nikal ke graph banate the aur answers nikalte the, Vahi hume reverse pattern follow krte the. Pehle answer aur uske baad values manipulate krte the. PHY101 ki first lab me hi TA se mera ladai krna and all. Vahan se jo bond develop hua vo aaj usse kahi jyada strong hai. Iss bond ka bas ek hi reason hai aur vo hai Sainik School. Uske baad CHE courses me saath baithna, Labs saath me krna aur courses to humne saath me paar kiye jisme pata hi nahi lagta tha kya chal raha hai lekin humne paar kr liye. CHE352 me bhi saath me lab krna aur report bana. Labs aur classes ke incident to jitne likhu kam hain.
Sports ki baaton me to alag feel aa jaati thi. Hum class me baithke apne apne sports ki baatein discuss krte the ek doosre se ki kya chal raha. Hockey ki bahut baatein discuss ki aur assignments chaapna, lekin kabhi pakde nahi gaye. 4 saal kaise saath me nikal gaye pata hi nahi chala.
Logon ki insight to mai deta rehta hai aur tum samjh rahe kaun si insight ki baat kr raha mai. Poore campus ki uss type ki news mai tumhe batata tha jo mai collect krta tha various sources se.
Placemene me tumne to gazab hi machaya bhai. Jin logon ne preparation ki unka na hua lekin tumne bina preparation ke macha diya. Placement to bas ek step hai tumhare career me lekin mujhe pata hai jahan tumhara aim hai you can rock kyuki approach positive honi chahiye aur vo hai.
Bas thoda bura ye lag raha ki last ke days me saath nahi reh paaye varna shayad aur mauj masti krte 
lekin ho na saka. But jaldi hi milenge kyuki college khatam ho sakta hai lekin hamari friendship nahi. Ghar bhi apna paas paas hai to jaldi hi milenge. Aur phone pe to hamesha connected. Jab Sainik school gya tha tab roya tha aur jab usse nikala to aur jyada roya. leikn aaj Sainik school se nikalne vaali feeling aa rahi.........................
author: Aviral  Singh

text: Yo Vakul...........bhai shayad tum ho jiske saath maine sabse jyada time spend kiya summer camp me. Sabse jyada matches bhi tumse khele Summer Camp me aur morning session me apan dono saath me running krte the. Sanket to aage hi rehta tha to apan dono mast saath me running krte the. Bhai vo din aaj bhi sabse jyada miss krta hu. Vo sessions aur vo tera incident jab tum Video call kr rahe the Court ke andar se jo Avinash ne pakad liya tha. Mauka mila to jaroor khelenge kyuki vo din aaj bhi bahut miss krta hu. Vo Arpit ki lena, Sanket ka Dosa laana other teams ke players se aur bhi bahut kuch..........Bas aaj tak ye nahi pata chala paaya ki tera kuch tha ya nahi.........you know what I mean.........Uske baad Placement me jo tumne machaya hai Shortlist hone me..........tabahi laa di thi...........Bhai happy for you ...........jaise ho mast vaise rehna......milte hain jaldi tab tak ke liye Tata..........
author: Aviral  Singh

text:
Hey Kanishka, the first time I contacted you was regarding the project under Prof. Vishal Agarwal because you were doing project under him. I guess you were more happy than me when I got an opportunity to work under him. During the second year summer, I learnt various things about the project from you regarding the project, got the help from you again and again for a small problem in the project. You taught me how to use VASP and HPC and all the stuffs. It was great to spent time with you during the project. During the third year we started talking a little more due to almost same courses. After that we started taking the same  OE courses before discussion and the things went on. Then the random calls and discussion about the internship, life and all the silly stuffs. Ransom talks
about the professors and all.  I guess you don't have cheated much during the exams before college life but you started that in the PHY473A also. Doing the crypto  in the same group was a lot fun. We spent whole day in cracking the DES but at last we figured out that our code is wrong. Also PHY690W was also a fun with you. You shown extraordinary performance by writing the codes in the last moment. It was one of my best group to work with you in PHY690W, raat me PPT banana
and report late me submit krna, all the things were fun. Assignments bhi bahut tumse copy kiya aur pakde nahi gaye. At last I want to say that stay happy as be cheerful as you are. Hope we will meet soon kyuki you have lot of pending treats that you said to give me. tab tak Bye rahega.
author: Aviral  Singh

text:

author: Ayush  Jain

text: Hey bro, It's been a long time since I've known you and one thing I can say for sure is that we started off as brothers and we will go off as brothers. You were always the guy I used to get positive motivation from. Very active, sporty, always optimistic, always on time and always planning ahead is how I would describe you. You were always so punctual, that I used used to rely on you more than my alarm (remember all my wake-up texts on the night before each exam). From our random bulla sessions to our OS assignment hangouts to my last day photoshoot, all moments go into my memory-bag. I still remember the night when your laptop erased a full-day worth of OS code you had written and you still had the determination to write all of that again. We planned to hit the gym together so many times, but it never happened :(. I still hope that you go to the gym with me someday in the future or maybe at least teach me your basketball tactics :P. I wish you all the best for all your future endeavours, and no doubt you will succeed in whichever avenue you proceed. Hope to meet you soon!!
author: Ayush  Kumar

text: Another god and dassa king of IITK, you are one the smartest people and one with the most crisp sense of humor that I have known at IIT Kanpur. I was fortunate to get to do Codefundo with you and Abhyuday and then going for ICPC regionals together (we defnitely nailed our first attempt üòÖ) and then David's Auquan. You are the kind of guy who always has an elaborate plan for an apocalypse and will succeed at everything no matter how adverse the conditions are. Also thanks a lot for helping me out when I lost my 3rd year internship, you always have some of the best ideas to offer. I will always remember the times in class when you raised a completely out-of-the-box doubt baffling the professor as well üòõ. Will definitely buy your book once it comes out into the market. And yeah, dogecoin is definitely not going to the moon üòî. Have a great time in the UK, and do invite us for a Europe tour!! ‚ù§Ô∏è
author: Ayush  Kumar

text:
Math God, Active Procrastinator, Pizza Lover, ChocoPie Distributor and what not!! You were my closest friend at IITK and my goto person for doubts, questions, random bulla, scientific/unscientific talk, help, enlightenment, imaginative theories, jokes, depression talk, w**d, or literally anything that a human could think of. There are so many memories we have together that it is hard to recall all of them. You started off as a quiet smart guy, but soon became our teacher in every course. I vividly remember the long tiring talk you gave on Goodstein's Theorem in the first year which none of us quite understood but it was still so fun listening to it. The canteen and pizza hangouts were my favourite. Pepper Barbecue Medium (plus an extra slice from my pizza), Maggi and Cheese Frankie was the the only thing you ever ate üòõ. Your room was like an open theatre of knowledge. One could come in at any time of the night, and be certain to leave with a substantial amount of mathematical/philosophical knowledge üòõ. 

You helping me to my feet when I was down was the norm, whether it was the Antaragni night when I was too hungover to walk, or the galaxy finals when I twisted my ankle hobbling down the stairs in excitement. It was hurtful to see your love for S***** P remain unconfessed üò•. It goes without saying that you are one of the smartest people I've met, and the most intense and profound math lover, the most surprising thing is how you achieve this with your god level last-minute decision-making skills (maybe procrastination is the solution to all our problems). Nothing can replace the awesome 4 years (minus 1 üòì) I had with you. Wish you all the best in all your endeavors in the US (and in finding true love üòõ), hope to see you soon!! ‚ù§Ô∏è
author: Ayush  Kumar

text: Munmun, Haga, Harshaga, no matter what we call you, you'll always be the bubbly, cheerful, smiling guy I know. From dancing to searching research internships (remember going to senior dorms late night fishing for advice üòÖ), preparing for interviews (which I screwed up sadly üò™), collaborating in assignments and quizzes, NLP project, CS610 (we set a new benchmark for collaboration and bitching together üòõ) and the Goa Trip, we have been together through all these times. We first met in the dancing group where I quickly became the notorious fraudy, and you were the only one who gave me hope that maybe I wasn't the worst dancer (sorry lol üòõ). You were my goto person for personal advice, CS talk, random gossip, asking treats (none of which you ever gave üòî) and for help. Being an introvert, you were the much needed friend to pull me out of my bubble and help me meet other smart people (including you). How would I have ever learnt how to fake smile and click good photos if you weren't there as my mentor üòõ. You are the most honest and open friend I've had. I can literally talk to you about anything without thinking twice, because I know we are bros. Thank you for making my IITK life a hundred times happier, worthful and easier üòå. God knows what hole of depression I'd have been in had I not found you. I hope no matter how far away you are, do not forget what this emoji means üë¨, "Bhai hai tu mera..". Also, good luck in finding Korean women and do bring back Samsung Watches for me. Hope to see you soon!! ‚ù§Ô∏è
author: Ayush  Kumar

text: Hey there roomie and bro, frankly I can say that no one has heard more of your weird-ass alarm-tone than me üòõ. It was a nightmare sleeping everyday knowing that I'll have to wake up to that very irritating alarm ü•∫. Right from the beginning you seemed like a very chill guy and I was quite satisfied when I found out who my roommate was üòÑ. I'm glad you were there in my room to prevent me from turning into an ultimate unsocial creepy maggu üòÖ, which I definitely would have become if you weren't there. You were my much needed distraction from study to keep me sane and healthy, not to mention the immense help I got from you in TA101. I distinctly remember your infinite shoe collection and how you had one shoe for every different activity üòõ. I also remember the great standoff between me and satpathy over who should get the B5 wing and you came in at the end to save the day. I'm so happy to see how you have been able to maintain your long-distance relationship for so long, kudos for that!! I would definitely need some good relationship advice from you in the future üòå. All the best for your masters and all your future pursuits, hope to see you soon!! ‚ù§Ô∏è

text: are bhai suppu....apan toh dram eve mai saath hi the toh jaan gaye the...pehle mujhe laga ki tum ajeeb insaan ho...phir dheere dheere samajh aaya ki oh tum toh insights different perspective wale aadmi ho...tumhari liye us din izzat badh gayi..dukh is baat ka hai ki tumse kabhi gyaan nahi le paaya..shukla loki dono se le liya...tumhe is ek mahine aana chhaiye tha campus par koi na....aasha karte hai ki tumse jald milenge aur sunnenge tumhari story..jao aur reserach karo aur noble leke aao...aur apni life enjoy karo...jald milenge
author: Ayush  Shrotriya

text: aur bhai tg kaise ho...pehle toh uss photu ke liye dil se shukriya.....iske baad....nayi job ke liye badhayi....iske baad advice...bandi aati jaati rahengi ab toh paisa bhi aa gaya bt mai pade rehna is never good humare saath enjoy karo....phir iske baad.....kaafi fun loving person to say but it all depends on your mood which i don't know is a good thing or bad thing :)....kaha se suru karein...waise jaane toh tumko late the par bhi enjoy kaafi kiya...woh intern prep ke time mt jaana tumhare paiso ki chai peena...intern na lagne ki bt saath khana...phi apan teeno ki lag jaane ke baad oat ki terrace pe life ka meaning search karna....tumhare ghar nahi aa paya yaar diwali pe aur tum bhi bulane nahi aaye is baat ka dukh hai....tumhara mujhe placement prep ke liye motivate karna(gaand phadne wala tareeka)....kaafi memories banayi...aur phir memories ka pitara galaxy ko toh kaise hi bhul sakte...photu club ko sambhalne ke liye shukriya mr. udgosh manager....iss ek mahine bhi kaafi saath raha..wo tumhara beamer phekna...bc sar pe lag jaye ball toh mar sakta aadmi....phir mera tumhara maje lena..waise mujhe malum nahi tha ki tum gussa ho gaye iske liye sorry..par bt mai pade rehna is not good..ab toh bhai ke pass gold hai crypto curr hai andha paisa hai toh ghar ke bahar line lag jayegi.....anyways that was a good time....aasha karte hai aapke sapne poore ho...life ke liye all the best....ummed karte hai ki jald milenge tum treat doge aur ghar bula loge....until next time..
author: Ayush  Shrotriya

text:
hello yatin...bsbe....boobies...kaise ho...kaha se suru karein...second year se karte hai..first year mai toh zyada ache se nahi janta tha..bagal wala room tumhare wo chutiyape aaj bhi smile le aate hai...summer mai tumhare room pe patte khelna...khud korean dekhkar tumhe spoiler dena...bsdk band karde korean dekhna...tumhare saath ladayi...haath mai sariya ghusne ke liye sorry...pehle mujhe kuch random points pe feel hota tha ki tumhare maje nahi lene chhaiye par mai jaise hi tumhari side leta tha tum hug dete the...but all in all kaafi innocent ho aisa kaha ja sakta hai...aur bsdk dusro ko khilana suru kar do..35 lakh logo ka ctc nahi hota tumhara income tax hai......realize karo bsbe ki tum ande ameer ho....iss ek mahine toh itni zyada mulaqat nahi hui..hui par kam...hall bhi alag aur late bhi aaye tum...par tumko jaanke maja aaya in chaar saalo mai...aage ki life ke liye all the best...ummed karta hu ki tum kabhi hume apne ghar bulaoge governor ke ghar chai ke liye leke jaoge :)...#BeakerGod....#BSBELegend...#AndaAmeer...
Tum bas investment karna seekh lo tumhe koi job nahi karni padegi...bahut paisa hai ghar mai...saara apne chote bhai ko le jaane de doge kya?

author: Deeksha  Yadav

text:
White headband, red hair tie, and the shrill voice which silenced everyone during freshers' practice in first year- that's how I'm always gonna remember you.
Our common trips to the washroom and your 'Hello Deeeksha' with that trademark smile comprised most of our interactions all these years.
You're really dedicated and full of surprises. Wish you the best for future!
Hoping to see you soon.
author: Deeksha  Yadav

text:
Yo roomie!
The cutie who used to get up and take a bath at 8 am everyday.
The one who slept with socks on (even in summer) to avoid catching cold.
The one who remained troubled about a lot of things but still kept calm.

text:
I remember my first all-nighter in IITK. First year, sitting in your room (E-101), playing CONTACTüòÇ and then getting into some deep philosophical shit till morning(as would become typical). From then to my last all-nighter, sitting on the path in front of A-Block, wondering how our time at IITK will be coming to an end and how we‚Äôll make the most of it, it has been hell of a ride. Through all the years at IITK, I‚Äôm glad we shared all those talks, some sober and some drunk af. 
Also that birthday surprise you all gave, hard shit to forgetüòÅ. It was one of my best moments at IITK.
Finally, I‚Äôve said this before, and I‚Äôll say it again you are the person whom I‚Äôve seen evolve the most in IITK and I greatly admire and respect you for it.

text: Chaapu bhai,
author: Devendra Kumar Meel

text:
Hello Pal! Kaisa hai bro? 
Having you in the same college was probably the best thing that happened to me in these four years. Our bond goes back to school when you joined it in 2012. 10th tk mai terko khaas nhi jaanta tha but 11th se tumne reputation bna hi li thi A section ke sbse chaapu launde waali üòÇüòÇüòÇ. Phr 12th mai thodi baat hoti rehti thi ki haa yar IIT jaana hai dono ne. Mujhe yaad hai 12th mai, Sunday breakfast ke baad kabhi kabhi tu Singh house ke saamne aaya krta tha aur vaha hum yehi discuss krte the ki yar bs IIT hojaae. 
When we passed out from school, I never thought that we‚Äôd still get the chance to see each other for at least the next five years. We got so lucky. 
Fortunately, we got the same batch in Resonance and so I had a friend in RJ1. Kota mai times kaafi hard the yar mentally but having you by my side in classes really helped me get through them. Hum class mai aksar saath baithte the and it was so much fun, pata nhi 1.5 1.5 ghante ke lectures kaise jhele humne bhaiüòÖüòÖüòÖ Kher jaise bhi jhele, they were worth it. Mujhe abhi bhi yaad aata hai kaise hum 15 min break hota tha jo classes ke beech, usme 5th floor pe jaake patties khaya krte the, Allen kee sheets pe üòÇ. Kota mai mai tere room bhi aksar aaya karta tha, specially Diwali ke baad se, aur bhut accha lagta tha yar vaha aake. Hum sab jb bahar khana khaane jaate the, vo tea breaks and bahar se paneer laake room pe khaana. Tumhare heater mai roti pe ghee lagake paratha bnana. It was all so much fun. Kabhi kabhi jb Kota yaad aata hai, aisa lagta hai vo din bhut mst the (aisa us time kabhi socha nhi tha ki ye din bhi yaad aaenge üòÇ). Pr baat yehi hai ki vo din islie yaad aate hai kyunki bhai humne saath mai itne maje jo kie. 
Phr bhagwaan ki dua se hum IITK aagye, jo ki bhut hi mst hua yar. Tune mujhe starting ke  days mai cycle road pe chalana sikhaya tha üòÇ, aaj ke din ye bhut hi simple sound krra hai mujhe but then it was a big deal for me. Hum un 2 3 din campus ke round maara krte the and it was so much fun. Tu mujhe kehta rehta tha, ‚Äú Peeche waala break maara kar, aage waale break se phisal skte hai‚Äù. Million dollar advice hai bhai ye, iss advice ki vajah se hi mai 4 saal IITK mai salamati se cycle chalata raha, including barsaat mai bhi. 
First year kaafi sahi nikla yar, hum class mai saath baith paate the, courses bhi same the aur kaafi accha lagta tha. Merko yaad hai ek baar August mai bhut baarish hui thi, roads pe paani bhara hua tha and mera chashma toot gya tha, to tu mere saath Kanpur city aaya tha chashma banwaane. Thankyou so much for that bro. Mujhe pata tha kit ere alawa koi nhi hai jo mere saath aaega and islie maine bs tujhe call kia. 
Phr hume ek din OAT mai Shekhar bsb mil gye and tu Hockey mai chala gaya. Bhai I am so happy that you found hockey, vaha tujhe bhut naye bande mile and you had the chance to grow so much with them. You found a family there and got a reason to work hard, stay fit and you found a purpose overall. Haa tu humesha khush nhi tha hockey mai, kabhi kabhi bhut frustrate ho jaata tha politics se aur Inter-IIT jaane ki team list se, but overall kaafi accha raha tere lie. Khaali room pe baithke dimaag kharab hi hota hai, ye tune jo 1 sem hockey miss kia us time dekh hi lia hoga. I personally think hockey helped you build a great personality. Tu pehle kaafi shy tha, ab sbse easily baat kr leta hai and indirectly hockey brought you many opportunities like working in Council and Udhgosh. 
2nd and 3rd year mai kaafi mulakaat hui and kabhi kabhi bahar party pe bhi jaaya krte the hum Shekhar bsb ke saath. Kaafi maja aata tha. Mai kbhi kbhi tere room pe aa jaata tha, aur kbhi kbhi hum tere wing ki chatt pe baith jaate the. Yar mst memories hai ye, humaari baatein bhut masaledaar rhi hai humesha üòÇüòÇüòÇ and mujhe yaad aaengi mujhe. Koi nhi ab phone pe baat krenge jb tk mil nhi paaenge. 
Kota and IITK mai tu mera support system tha bro. Jab bhi mera dimaag kharab hota tha from the pressure, stress ya koi aur baat hoti thi, mai tujhi ko sbse pehle batata tha and you were always there for me and never used to turn me away. You always listened to me patiently before giving me any advice. Thankyou so much for that bro!
You have worked very hard in life, Anshuman. Even Ghorakhal aane se pehle se hi tu bhut mehnat krta aara hai. Jo tu 3rd class mai Olympiad mai rank laaya tha use bhi pehle se. And you have also achieved so much in life because of that and the many sacrifices you have made along the way. At times, life will get tougher bro, specially with the UPSC preparation, but tu himmat mt haarna bhai. Kuch bhi ho jaae lage rehna. Mai tere alaawa aur kisiko nhi jaanta jo itna deserve krta hai UPSC nikaalna. And I know you will work very very hard for it. I believe in you with all my heart. Mujhe pata hai a few years down the line you will make it. It will be so great to see you succeed again and again in life. So keep going. Jaada kabhi stress ho to I am only one call away bhai. Vaise bhi itni koi dikkat nhi hai, mai call krta rahunga tujhe time to time. 
Wishing you an awful lot of success, fulfilment and prosperity in life bro. Stay healthy and happy forever. Aur haa, keep smiling bhai. Terpe smiling face hi jachta hai. 
Keep in touch bro. (Goobye nhi kehra kyunki hum humesha milte rahenge.)
author: Dhawal  Raturi

text:
Hello Shrotriya bhai! Kaise ho?

Bro 2nd year se jb tu MTH ke lectures mai Goel ke saath aas paas baithne laga, tbse tumse dosti hui. Us time laga to nhi tha but aakhir humne MTH ke courses pure kr hi lie. Humara jo satti waalo ka group ha, usme tum ek atthi ho and also sbse jaada serious the exams and quizzes ke lie humesha. Thank you for that bro because bhut baar mai pd nhi raha hota tha upcoming tests ke lie aur tu mujhe aake bolta tha bhai pdle, quiz hai agle hafte ya end sem hai agle hafte and that would make me prepare from an earlier date and perform better.  Intern time pe bhi tune mujhe kaafi baar motivate as well as guide kia tha.

Bhai tere saath MTH ke alawa kisi topic pe jaada discussion hua nhi kbhi but from the three years that we spent doing courses together, ye samajh aagya ki you are a mst insaan. Mai kbhi tha to nhi drams mai pr suna bhut ijjat hai tumhaari vaha. Bhai apna ye I-don‚Äôt-give-a-darn-about-what-you-think waala attitude kbhi mat chorna aur aise hi life mai fearless hoke aage bdna!!!

Thank you for all you have done for me bro. I am really grateful that our paths crossed in these four years and that we got the chance to become friends. You are a hard-working person and I wish you great success, fulfilment, and prosperity in life. Stay healthy and happy bro. Take care!

P.S. I still can‚Äôt believe you are graduating at 19 and started college at 15.

text:
Hello bro, I saw you the first time when you asked a question regarding branch change on the very first day of our orientation. And over those seven days, I saw you standing up, taking the mic and asking the same question probably a million times moreüòÇüòÇüòÇ Who would have thought, we'd cross paths in these four years. 
Although you weren't always contributing üòúüòú, it was great to have you in the TA project team in the second year. You are cool bro, a great guy to have small chats with. And so we did, the numerous times in mess when we ate together and other times about the tragedy of having MnSC as our major, lol. We even had the same alumni buddy for a while ( who you'd stopped calling and used to asked me about you üòÇüòÇüòÇ, like where did Chindrala vanish?). 
It was fun to know you bro. You got a PPO and I am very happy for you. May we meet again someday. Till then take care and stay happy. Wishing you great success and fulfilment. Bye!
author: Dhawal  Raturi

text:
Hello Jay bhai! Humaari branches bhi different thi aur hall bhi. It was so unlikely that we‚Äôd ever cross paths in these four years, but I am glad that we did, thanks to basketball. The first time I talked to you was on the basketball court during one of the CPA practice sessions. We didn‚Äôt talk much in the first year but summer camp mai we became great friends (we‚Äôll always be great friends). 

Bhai summer camp mere in 4 saalo mai sbse best time tha and you were one of the reasons for it. Summer camp ka time yaad krta hu to aisa lagta hai jaise camp koi sapna tha, kyunki hum us time bs khate, khelte aur soya krte the. But vo time bhut mst tha yar aur jo humaari team thi vo bhi sb mst bnde the. Acads ki wajah se basketball continue nhi kr paae 2nd year Udhgosh ke baad se but dost to humesha hi rahenge. Ek baar tu aur mai raat ko cycle pe nikle the campus mai ghoomne, kaafi baari oat mai party bhi ki aur kabhi kabhi tu Ujjwal se milne aaya krta tha hall to mulaakat ho jaati thi. Pr jitni mulaakat hui, km hui yar. But jitni bhi hui unhike lie mai grateful hu.

Fourth year mai same hall mai to reh nhi paae but jo 10 12 din March ‚Äô21 mai saath basketball khela, bhut accha laga. Aisa laga jaise we were reliving the whole Summer Camp experience again. Basketball khelne ka alag hi maza tha IITK mai. 1 1.5 ghanta jb court pe hote the, aisa lagta tha jaise apni saari problems kuch time ke lie gaayab hogyi ho. 

Thankyou for all the experiences we had bhai. It has been so much fun to know you. I will miss you a lot. Terse baat krke humesha accha lagta tha because you used to listen so patiently. I wish you all the success in the world bhai. May you find your purpose and have a fulfilled and prosperous life. Stay healthy and happy. Take care bhai. Mst mst playlist share krte rehna. I‚Äôll stay in touch!

P.S. Congrats on the Amazon PPO. Mera bhai chaapega life mai mst!
author: Dhawal  Raturi

text:
Dipak Frickin‚Äô Mahajan!!! Bro, how are you doing? 
It was worthwhile to have you, Aditya and Shubham in the adjacent room in the freshman year. The memories that we made in that short time itself are priceless. I remember that time when a bunch of 3rd years from 2-Bot caught us so happy that they couldn‚Äôt bear it and took us to the lawn and asked me to sing and you to dance to it. I never told you, but I was terrified that night and the only reason I felt safe was that you were there with me and I thought, I have my friend by my side and whatever happens, we‚Äôll get through this together. Contrary to our apprehension, the night took a rather hilarious turn, and we got an anecdote to laugh our asses off for the rest of our lives. I remember those numerous nights, when you, Shubham and I used to get together and mess with anyone we could possibly find in the wing (mostly, Tamonud ‚Äì Sorry Tamonud!) and used to make so much noise that Aditya could never sleep. And I remember the night before the PHY103 midsem when we pulled a night out in CC and you helped me get through all the tutorials and notes so that I could pass the next day. And I did. 

I remember the few but glorious trips that we took to BBQ or malls to watch a movie. Also, the time you and Tamonud treated the whole wing there (We love you for it!). I remember the time we watched Avengers: Infinity War (me, you, Aditya and Tamonud) and had to walk kilometres afterwards to find a ride back to college (What a day it was!). 

I remember the times in the sophomore, junior and senior years when I called on you for advice and guidance and you never turned me away, and the times you watched out for me when I was crashing academically. I also remember the innumerable times you helped me find greater clarity about my life and the times you saw me through my various never-ending crises and ever-recurring crossroads. 
I thank you for every one of these times. Thank you for being by my side, thank you for taking the time, thank you for every one of your advice, thank you for all the fun times, thank you for everything. 

Lastly, may I add how breath-taking it was to have had the chance to watch you grow and become this fabulous individual that you have become. That stooped, awkward kid that walked uneasily through the gates of Hall 03 in July 2017, inconfident, is now this confident, mature and more-learned-than-ever leader that is walking out head held high with a blazing charisma, having touched and enriched hundreds of lives, including mine. The way that you have lived these four years, fully and joyfully, inspires me and will continue to inspire me throughout my life. It is an honour to know you and have you as my bhai. I was very lucky that our paths crossed and I, whole-heartedly and unconditionally, wish you the best in life. May you be a thousand times more successful than anyone who has ever lived, and may you rise to your full potential, because you are INFINITE my friend. You are a fricking star, so please be and stay that way¬†forever.
author: Dhawal  Raturi

text:
Hello Parshad bhai! Kya haal hai?
First year mai to jaada interaction nhi hua but jb MTH ne hum sb MTH waalo ki collectively leni shuru ki, it brought us closer, and we formed this awesome satti-guys-waala group, and it has helped us get through the MTH courses so successfully. Over time, you became one of the more serious and consistent persons in our group and all of us started looking to you during our academically intense times. 

Bro, the notes that you wrote on your iPad by attending every class, every day, helped us more in our courses than the professors themselves. Thanks to your notes, we got through all the exams and the quizzes almost smoothly üòú üòú üòú. Every time that I was suffering academically (because of my own deeds), I always knew I could fall back on you and your notes. At times, it must have frustrated you that I used to miss classes and then ask for your notes and help constantly but you never shied away from helping me. I don‚Äôt know if I even deserved to be treated in such a great way by you.  During the Internship season also, I came to you for advice and guidance a few times and you never turned me away. Thank you for being so well-informed and helpful all the time. In my 3rd and 4th year, when I was having trouble committing to academics, your dedication inspired me and motivated me to try and work harder. 

You are a genuinely great person bro. I enjoyed the few parties that we attended together, like Shrotriya‚Äôs 18th birthday in CCD (I can't believe that kid is graduating at 19!), the BBQ party, the pizza party in Urban Clave and the party in Hall 10 canteen.I think the video-editing that you do as freelancing is so over-the-top cool. It has enabled you to buy stuff for yourself, including that wicked CPU that you showed us one time in the group chat. You inspire me everyday to work harder on my dreams and also, to not wait on them but to work every day to achieve them.  

Thank you for all you have done for me. I am really grateful that our paths crossed in these four years and that we got the chance to become friends. You are a hard-working person and I wish you great success, fulfilment, and prosperity in life. Stay healthy and happy bro. Take care!

P.S. It‚Äôs just my gut feeling but I think you‚Äôd do great in the business world. I know that you have similar plans for yourself already and I think you‚Äôll be very successful. 
P.P.S. If I ever make some ‚Äòbig money' , it‚Äôs your start-up/business I‚Äôd want to invest it in.
author: Dhawal  Raturi

text:
Hello Ujjwal bhai! Kaise ho?

Humaari sabse pehle baat hui thi jb hum freshers inferno mai Hall 3 ke lie basketball khele the saath. Aur uske baad to CPA mai milna hota rehta tha. 

Pr tumhe acche se jaanne ka mauka to Summer Camp mai hi mila aur hum kaafi acche dost bhi bn gye. Bhai summer camp mere in 4 saalo mai sbse best time tha and you were one of the reasons for it. Summer camp ka time yaad krta hu to aisa lagta hai jaise camp koi sapna tha, kyunki hum us time bs khate, khelte aur soya krte the. Court se thakkr aate the aur jb so nhi rahe hote the to hasi majak chalta rehta tha. Vo time bhut mst tha yar aur jo humaari team thi vo bhi sb mst bnde the. 2nd year ke Udhgosh se maine basketball khelna chor dia tha but dost to humesha hi rahenge. 

Uske baad bhi kaafi baar mulakaat aur baatein hoti rahi. 2nd year mai saath SG bhi rahe aur hall mai kbhi kbhi mess ya quad mai milte rehte the. Ek shaam quad mai 3 bot ke saamne baithke humne dher saari baatein bhi ki thi sur apni problems bhi share ki thi ek doosre se. OAT mai saath milkar, basketball team ko humne birthday treat bhi krai thi. To mulakaate to bhut hui pr kaafi nhi ho paai kbhi pandemic ki vajah se, pr jitni bhi hui, uske lie mai bhut grateful hu bro. 

Tumne basketball 3rd year ke end tk continue rakha and actually you were the only one from our batch to do so. I have huge respect for you because of that. You were always deeply dedicated to everything you committed to, from studies to basketball. That's why I'm sure you'll do great in life and will rise to your maximum potential. 

Thank you for all the experiences we had bhai. It has been so much fun to know you. You are a genuinely good person. Also you are one of those very few people I've met, that think about life in long-term. Always take advantage of that. Terse baat krke humesha accha lagta tha because you used to listen so patiently and genuinely. I will miss you a lot brother. I wish you all the success in the world bhai. May you find your purpose and have a fulfilled and prosperous life. Stay healthy and happy. Take care bhai. I'll stay in touch. 

P.S. PhD aur research krne ka sapna kabhi mt chorna bro. Bhale hi due to pandemic, situation thodi tough hogyi hai but never give up on your dreams, ever.
author: Dhawal  Raturi

text:
Agar bhagwan khud bhi aake bolega ki SHAILABH jaisi RANDI kahi aur mil sakti hai to bhi nahi maanunga. Randi Rone ki definition hai bhai tu, ye kabhi mat bhuliyo, na hi badaliyo. Yahan sabse closest friends me se ek. Sabse kanjoos, harami aur jugaadu logo me se bhi ek. Par dependable aur Hai dil ka boht acha.
Shailabh Ji ki jai!!!!
Yaad to hoga hi jab teri vajeh se purana cooler thik kara ke puri summer chud gayi thi hamari ü§£. 3 saal se gym jane ki baat kari par gaya kabhi nahi. Wing ka ML gawd, paper pe paper publish karata rehta hai, abhi covid ke baad last 2 mahine bhi aaye to mostly paper ki zoom meetings me hi busy, Phir bhi extreme randi rona ki yaar "mujhse bada chutiya duniya me ho nahi sakta" - Ye sahi bhi hai aur galat bhi. 
Bithoor trip to yaad hogi vo lambi cycle ride aur boat rowing. Tere saath wali Manali trip sabse memorable cheezon me se ek hai mere liye bhai, saari hikings aur adventure sports, tere wall climbing skills bhi (inspired from CSE profs).
Ye covid wale last ke mahino me campus puri raat ghume, cards khele, khaya piya aur jam ke maze kare humne, last me long drive to Delhi bhi.
Adobe ML me pure campus me akela selection hone ke baad bhi aur upar jane ki teri bhookh yaad rahegi, neutron star milgaya par black hole ki bhookh.
Research me to tu aur upar jayega hi ye sabko pata hai.
Bas ye dukh hai ki ab mulakaat kam hogiü•∫.

author: Gunjan  Jalori

text:
CRINGE ALERT!!
It started with scaring other couples on the skywalk and ended with, NO, it never ended :). You can never imagine how much you meant to me at the time we met. You still have no idea how precious those late-night walks were, how beautiful the sun looked at 5 am with you, how you just understood what I meant, how you just knew what to say at every fucking time, how you always kept my priorities at top, how you never really complained about anything, how you made me laugh even if it wasn‚Äôt necessary. I know everything you did required patience and dedication, I know it wasn‚Äôt easy for you to get out of your comfort zone but there wasn‚Äôt even one single time when you backed out. You are the most rational boyfriend one could expect. Even when we were fighting, you were there for me. Many of the things can not be written here but I know you'll always feel them while reading this. I do and always will appreciate those little things, our walks on "footpaths" both inside and outside campus, our first date in bazooka, sneaking through moti jheel barricades, the gatecrash in Kanpur, binging tv series, our spot(wink) and infinite other things. I know I can get too competitive and sometimes it can be difficult but you never uttered a word. I am extremely happy for us to have crossed many challenges that came in our relationship. It was as close to ideal as WE could get. We had our quirks and weirdness. I like having really conversations with you, I love sharing the "we could go to jail for this" humor with you. I love that you typed my pet name exactly 69 times in my memoir. I love a million things about you and I can fill pages but can not. You'll know them. I just want to say one thing, there may be a thousand ways in which a relationship MAY or may NOT go, but I know we'll choose what will work best for us. LOVE YOU MOTU üñ§

PS:  Even if we decide to break up, I REALLY hope our friendship stays this magical. :)

text:
A youngster was attending a video conference with his Manager who was upset over the background noises. The Youngster turned around and told his grandmother to keep quiet.

She walked towards the youngster, to take a look into what he was doing and saw a person on the Monitor and asked, ‚ÄúWho is he?‚Äù

The youngster muted his audio and video and said, ‚ÄúHe is my Manager‚Äù.

She said, ‚ÄúI want to talk to your Manager‚Äù. But the youngster denied. By the time the Manager started pinging the youngster and the youngster unmuted to talk and his grandmother shouted, ‚ÄúManager I want to talk to you".

The Manager agreed and the youngster unmuted the video. The grandmother, with a smile said, ‚ÄúNamaste‚Äù and introduced herself and the Manager also greeted her.

She said, ‚ÄúYou look upset‚Äù.

The Manager said, ‚ÄúYeah, some kind of work tension, a lot of noise around your house and we are not able to complete the meeting in time‚Äù.

The Grand Mother asked, ‚ÄúMay I help solve your problem?‚Äù

Her grandson was stopping her and telling her to keep quiet.

The Manager said, ‚ÄúIt‚Äôs ok, let her speak‚Äù.

The Grandmother narrated, ‚ÄúOnce there was a Young man, who sat under a tree for taking rest. He was continuously hearing a bird‚Äôs sound. He lifted his head and seeing a bird, started chasing it, so that he could peacefully take some rest. The bird came closer to him and said, ‚ÄúYou are taking rest under my nest. I will not ask you to leave this place but you should learn to co-exist with us‚Äù.

The Grandmother looked at both of them and said, ‚ÄúYour Home is your nest‚Äù where you are supposed to take rest and bond with your dear and near ones. I do understand the Covid-19 situation, but you should also understand that our home is not your office.

When we come to visit our family members at your office place, we are expected to behave professionally or maintain a certain decorum.

Similarly, when you are using our home for your office work, you should understand the situation at our home.

There is nothing wrong with working from home, but remember, it is the family members benevolent nature, that is keeping the corporate world functioning today and the economy running.

She looked at the manager and asked, ‚ÄúAm I correct ?‚Äù

The Manager‚Äôs mother peeped and said "You are absolutely right‚Äù.
author: Harish  Dechiraju

text:
There are several things to consider before buying a product that contains the label ‚ÄúMade in China‚Äù.

Every purchase of a ‚ÄúMade in China‚Äù product directly supports the Chinese Communist Party (CCP). The corporate income tax rate is 15%-25% [1]. The CCP levies taxes on businesses which it uses to boost the power and influence the party possesses both in China and abroad. There was once the belief that China would become more democratic as it traded with the world. This prediction has never occurred. In fact, the CCP is stronger than ever before.

The Chinese Communist Party runs hundreds of concentration camps across the country, and your purchase of Chinese made products allow these abuses to continue. At the time of this writing, China has at least 1 million Muslim Uighurs in Chinese run concentration camps [2] where murder, rape, and torture are common occurrences [3]. There are also reports that describe how Chinese authorities are forcing minority women to undergo sterilization [4]. And these abuses detailed above are not just happening to Muslims. Christians, Buddhists, and the Kazakh are also imprisoned in these concentration camps [5] [6]. Women in the camps who do not sing patriotic communist songs or praise president Xi Jinping are raped and electrocuted repeatedly [7].

China suppresses freedom of expression. Communist authorities routinely detain, persecute, and jail people for crimes such as ‚Äúspreading rumors‚Äù and ‚Äúinsulting the countries leaders‚Äù, according to Human Rights Watch [8] and Amnesty International [9].

China allowed the so-called ‚ÄúCOVID-19‚Äù virus to proliferate in its own borders before it became a pandemic. When Dr. Li Wenliang, the ‚ÄúWuhan Whistleblower‚Äù, alerted his community that a strange new virus was killing people, Chinese Communist authorities jailed him where he subsequently died from COVID-19 in jail [10]. The CCP then censored all information about the virus. Eventually, it jumped the border and became a worldwide pandemic.

text:
Firstly, Biotech/BSBE is NOT Biology. It is a proper engineering field with ample math, coding and physics involved.
BSBE at IITK is a wonderful place to be at, 
however I must correct you its very different from the curriculum of 'biotech' at IITD or IITR.
BSBE here will, in your four years, give you a good insight into a variety of fields in the given branch - Microbiology, Biochemistry, Biotechnology, Biochemical Engineering, Neurobiology, Computational Bio, Biophysics. In addition to this, its a highly practical field with a lot of application based approach.
The best part is the huge growing sector of BSBE in the world and its intersection with all the branches that exist today.
Take any branch name and add biology next to it - you will get a highly demanding field of biotechnology which is very lucrative in terms of research.
Example - Computational Bio and Neuroscience; Bioelectricity; Biochem engg; Biophysics; Biochemistry; Biomaterials...
Also, I can assure that irrespective of a persons former background, they can ace these subjects easily and go on for masters in any of the intersections in the future.
Hectic: No
Opportunities : Infinite, not in corporate jobs, but research oriented fields.
Money : Really good, once a person has done specialisation/masters, and is sincere enough.
#thatsiitk

text:
This is an extroverts view on the world and on the "problem" that introverts cause.

To me? You all talk too much, you waste words and time. You're a distraction to what actually matters and more often than not you're detracting from the world, not adding to it with your insightful conversations.

Now I don't blame you for it, I don't think me better. But I do not want to talk to you, I do not need to talk to you. I enjoy myself more without the empty words being exchanged. My extrovert partner? We have comfortable silences with entire conversations taking places with looks, squeezes of the hand, and facial expressions.

Something you consider awkward might not feel that way to me, while your natural flowing conversation feels forced. If I wanted to share something with you I would, but honestly I probably wouldn't find it often necessary and when I did it's not some word shattering revelation it simply something I found worth saying in the same way you find all the words you use worth saying.

No more important, no less.

It feels like you find the silence awkward and blame that awkwardness on the individual. When really they're likely comfortable with it and find the conversation awkward. If I wanted to talk to someone I would, it's not introversion that would stop me from having a conversation it would be anxiety and to me that's something else entirely.

text:
I have been programming (not "coding", how awfully, you kids these days, say) powerful DOS programs in assembly since 1999 and I don't know any of your hipster node.js bullshit that makes you look "cool". Seriously, get that shit outta here. You're just making yourself look like clowns typing some incomprehensible sugarified as fuck bullshit, half of which, in fact, is written by your brand new and shiny Electron-based text editor you enjoy every second of, and the other half of which, is copied from fucking StackOverflow. Look, we didn't even fucking have that and we did shit, and you suckers can't even spend a single second without it. You spend hours looking for a gorgeous and flawless color scheme for it so your so-called "coding" is always a pleasure for you. We didn't even fucking have IntelliSense or linters, you fucking spoiled little brats. Stop making programming look like a joke and go back to your parents' basements, where you are truly who you are.

Burn HTML. Burn CSS. Burn JavaScript. Burn PHP. Burn the fucking web.

I bet you won't even be able to fucking stand writing some C for an embedded system without crying to your mommy

... about how there are so fucking many compilers errors and everything went not as you expected.

You call C fucking unsafe? Look at JavaScript. Look at PHP. They let you pull out insane bullshit while you don't even notice. And then you spend hours trying to find out what you did wrong.

C is actually useful.

Everything you fucking see on your screen has atleast 60% of C or C++ in it.

Oh, what is JavaScript useful for? Rolling a stupid fucking dropdown menu or a sexy as fuck banner animation?

I know what you're thinking.

And by the way, CSS is fucking stupid.

It makes no sense half and a quarter of the time.

Web development is gross.

And you know it.

You try to compensate it by making dumb frameworks that require ages to load because they weigh over 16MiB for no fucking reason, but it is no use.

Oh, I wonder why none of you said anything yet.

Probably because I just roasted you all hard and you can't deny it.

author: Jai Ranjan Sharma

text:
Careful Jay. It's Ms Flamme here. 

Jab starting me aaya tha to itni entropy expect nhi ki tha. Silly me? Haan partly. College me aa rhe ho, how do you expect everything to go so nice n cheese, but spare me thoda sa, mai itna bhi guilty nhi because aane ke 2-3 din me hee ek ladki se milna hua. Vo mere bagal me hi baithi thi, sab theek tha, itne me hi vo achanak meri taraf mudi, aur ek shabd boli. Ek, sirf ek. Samajh to nhi paya mai us samay kya hua, kya ho gya. Samajh to aaj bhi nhi paya hu par us shabd ki uttejna usi pal se alag ho gyi zindagi bhar ke liye. Usne kajal lagaya tha, badi hi pyaari lag rhi thi vo.

Tujhe yaad hoga ki humne numbers exchange nhi kiye the bade time tak. Mudreka ke thru milte the, hawa ki philosophy discuss krte the. God ki existence ko brutally destroy aur defend kiya. Self ki depths ko, heights ko, beliefs ko, connects ko, sab kuch test hua, sab kuch test kiya. Discussions bohot hue. Aur in sab ke beech pata chala tu jitni thoughts me rebel hai, utni hi life me bhi.

Tu ye jaanti hogi Gunjan ki walks pe bohot saari mast crazy baate ki, par tu ye nhi jaanti hogi ki in walks ke pehle mai padh ke aata tha, prepare krke aata tha. Tujhe ye realisation hoga Gunjan ki teri company special to thi, par tu ye nhi jaanti hogi ki isse pehle kabhi itna tense nhi hua. Tu shayad is chij se bhi aware hogi Gunjan ki tere liye vo poem ek din me likhi thi, par tu ye nhi jaanti hogi ki us din ke baad mai aajtak koi poem complete nhi kar paya. Bohot attempts liye, abhi bhi ek pe kaam kr rha par yet koi complete nhi kr paya. 

2nd year me aaye, milna kam ho gya. Jaha hafte me roz milte the aur 2-3 baar ghumne chale jaate the, vaha ab dikhna bhi naseeb me nhi hua. Tu padhai me dhyan laga rhi thi, mai pata nhi kya kr rha tha. Time tha, time kam nhi pada par ye bhi sach hai ki hum nhi mile itna jitna pehle milte the.

Nhi socha tha ye gap badhta hi chala jayega. Beech beech me sparks the. Diro bungalow ke bahar us raat ki light setting imprinted hai man me, rhegi aur anant tak. Vo chaurahe ke aage road kinare mandir se emanating green light yaad hai? Tune hath pakad ke aur dara diya tha. Baate jab bhi hui tere sath, acchi hui. It's hard to find koi aur un baato ke liye. Kam hone lagi, par vo elements the. Vo glory thi. Shayad apne apne raaste pakad liye. Antaragni ho gyi, mere bahane khatam. Ek din room pe aya tere. Us din samajh aayi. Baat kr rhe the, teri aankhein nam ho gyi. Mujhe maaf krna Gunjan. I learnt life me kuch us din. Won't go down that fucking lane ever again. 

Mai kabhi concede nhi krna chahta, na krunga ki tu cute hai. Par ab samajh gya hu. Pehle mai delusional tha, ab denial me hu. Tu hai cute, aur nhi bhi. 

If there's a bond I care and value about so much in my life, it's with you. Abhi bhi waaqif nhi ise kya kehte hain, but the day it comes to it, I'll put up a good fight, take note of that! Hey, aisa ho skta hai ki kinhi moments me dikhe nahi, but stay there na, call me up, and ask me blunt up front. I'll take responsibility of rest. 

Listening to T wala song. You're the one, suit, for it. Ms Flamme, üíö
author: Jai Ranjan Sharma

text: - BHATIA. The name jo sabse jyada famous hoga Y17 mein. Ain‚Äôt I a lucky person jo 800 logon mein se kuch ginti ke 15-20 (may be tere case mein 30-40) logon mein se hai jo tere liye memoir likh rahe and jiske liye hopefully tu bhi likhega? (Of course, is taunt-cum-joke ke bina to memoir adhura hi rehta.) So I think we at first majorly bonded through Intern nahi lagna, then same jagah lagna. And then our common hatred in form of dosti (maan le ab to. Dosti to hai) for Nikunj. Nikunj ko vaise to bohot taane maare, ‚Äútune aaj tak kiya hi kya hai‚Äù but I think apan dost na hote vo na hota to. So we have to give this one to him. Vaise tere saath bhi thik thak ghuma hun campus mein majorly I think Antaragni 3rd year. And vo outreach cell ki chat kaafi extraordinary to obviously nahi thi but I think mujhe aaj se 10 saal baad bhi yaad rahegi. Lockdown hone se pehle jaa paaye. Now when I think tu kaafi straight forward hai plans mein. Seedha ‚Äúchallen?‚Äù then mein  ‚Äúhaan chal‚Äù. Koi jyada sochna nahi. Vaise you were among a handful of people jisko maine first judgement mein galat judge kiya hoga. Reasons to tujhe pata hi honge :). Bahar se jitna cool and doesn‚Äôt care vaala attitude tha utna hi overthinker and dosti nibhane vaala nikla.  Tha esliye likha taaki tu overthink naa kare ki tu abhi bhi overthinker hai ya nahi. Vaise first time to image neutralise tab ki thi jab second year mein (mostly) apan C mid ki stairs pe bhet ke baat kar rahe the. Topic bhi yaad hai mujhe vaise. But haan apan second year mein hi dost ban gaye the be. I think tu lockdown mein ghar pe jokes rehearse kar karke sabse funny banda ban gaya hai group ka. Bhale hi is journey mein tune kitno ko offend kiya ho. Kabhi sorry bol de unhe. ‚ÄúWas just trying to be funny‚Äù. Pehle ek dam offensive statement bol kar has deta tha. Sabko hi bolna pad jaayega Bio mein jod le. Vaise kaafi maje karte yaar intern mein. Mein to kaafi soch rakha tha. Hopefully ab job mein kar paaye despite the distance and all. Aise hi kabhi bol dena call karke ‚Äúchal‚Äù to chal lenge.
author: Jay  Mundra

text: Roomie. First person at met at IITK. Ajeeb si dadhi vaala ensaan jo mujh se 4 saal badha lagta tha. Apan dono kaafi time to room mein nahi rahe saath mein. Ya to mein nahi hota tha ya tu nahi. But I guess apne mein kaafi understadning thi and that‚Äôs why we were voted best roomies. Bas es baat ko chhod ke ki mein us side vaala bed le liya dono sem :p. Still remember vo tere late night calls. Kaafi irritating the. And jo tu 1-2 baar legit neend se bhet kar kuch lines bol raha tha lol. Also man never thanked you for this but when my dadi passed away and I was trying to sleep. You just came in hugged and said few lines. That was way too comforting tujhe shayad yaad naa ho. Generally aise moments par pata nahi hota hai kya bola na hai but tu shayad kaafi mature tha. Vaise tujhe dekh kar generally first year yaad aa jaata hai may be because uske baad interaction bhi kam raha. Anyways, kuch alag kar life mein and keep in touch and rupee vapas kar de xd.
author: Jay  Mundra

text: Tere saath kaafi hangout to nahi kiya but IPL time tum jaise logon ke karan hi interesting tha. Akele dekhne mein kya maja. Jaise es baar tu,bihari tha nahi to mosly room pe akela dekhta tha. You and your obsession for hockey man. Kitna khela tu. vaise deep conversations bhi hui hai apni tujhe yaad ho to vo bhi thodi lambi. Bas kam hui. Aur haan MI se nafrat hai mujhe kyonki kuch jyada hi acche players hai. Sab international level ke hai usme bhi best. And tumhari team ko football mein haraya tha jo jyada mat udo. Thik hai :). Chal man keep your hockey vaala dedication and fire alive. To life mein kaafi chaap dega.
author: Jay  Mundra

text: Since Hindi mein likha to tu bolega, ‚Äú etni hindi padhi nahi jaati‚Äù I will try to write a major portion in English. So, where to start from.  First of all thanks for my CPI. I think one of the differences between my first year CPI and the overall CPI is you. We did not interact much in the first year compared to what followed later i.e. barging into your room all the time. So, thanks for that 0.5 vaala part. Since, Nikunj would have already written ki tu IITK ka sabse accha insaan hai, I would try to skip that part. You deserved to become an SG more than nikunj or I of course. Man, now when I am thinking besides being an accha insaan, thanks for all the motivation you have given me while my RnD Rona. Maybe you were morally obliged to do so at that time because of your nature but still, you always responded the way an RnD rona should have been addressed. I think among all my friends, sabse jyada time there saath spent kiya. And what can I say about your weird cheezen? Hanging up the phone after the other person so that it‚Äôs not rude. That ‚ÄúByee‚Äù, ‚Äúthi thi thi‚Äù vaali haasi and literally many more. In habits ki vajah se hi tere saath hangout karna was sabse jyada fun. (Not saying you were the most fun person or the funniest but hangout karna was sabse jyada fun. Confusion naa ho.) Itne ghanto mein bhi kabhi bore nahi hua. Also I literally never had to check the courses or anything while preregistration. Tu bata deta tha ‚Äú yeh lo lo, bohooot kaam ka hai‚Äù and agar koi prof ka review choot jaata to vo nikunj bata deta tha. Campus aana tha bro. Logon ko lagta hai tu badal gaya kaafi. Mujhe lagta hai kaafi to nahi badla but ab vo ‚Äúcute and gullible‚Äù Neil naa raha ho. Sudhar jaaa. Thoda kam pyaar mein pada kar. Dono ladkiyon as well as laundon se xd. Also, my first memory of us is campus tour bus. Not sure vo bathroom ki line ke pehle tha ya nahi. Esse yaad aaya tu roz subah yeh gaana suna tha bathroom mein ‚Äúsubah subah, yeh kya huva..‚Äù. Lol. Neil and Niki pe dance karna reh gaya. Chill hai. I am hoping ki apan to mil hi lenge yaar.
author: Jay  Mundra

text: Tune memoir jyada hi accha likh diya. Can‚Äôt match that 19-20 vaala pun but lets‚Äô try. We met on the first day of orientation obviously. Vaise poore orientation ke baad bhi tere se etni jyada achhi bonding nahi thi. May be because Jay and mein poore time batiyate rehte the and tu side mein aadhe time bore hoti rehti :p. Sorry for that xd. But I guess PE mein acchi bonding ho gayi thi and then batti club ke time bhi touch mein thi. Uske baad I guess touch choot gaya. Also, I do remember first lady vaale jokes but yaad nahi aa raha mein presi kyon tha :). Kaafi late realise hua (pata to pehle bhi that) ki tu bhi Maheswari hai vo bhi bina H  and etni cheezen common hai apne ghar mein. Milte hai kabhi. Keep in touch.

text:
Tumhare toh kya hi kehne, bohot kuch h likhne ko!!! Outside wing, campus me mera sabse zyada time tumhare saath spend hua h. DesCon summer project se hm mile the, exactly toh nhi pta kahan pr mile the. But phir secy bne aur coordi. Ekbaar techkriti ke kisi finance event me part liya tha, meine , tumne aur shrey ne.  Tum dono mere hmesha mze lete the bohot, shrey sabse zyada tum thoda kam. Think it through me last me vo hmne, Anshul ne tie kraya tha, vo hmesha yaad rhega. Aur vo senate hall memeetings me jaane ka alas hmdonoka ,ekbaar secy ko hi bhejdiya tha. Aur juniors keliye Descon summer projects toh tumhare bhrose hi hue the. Voh raatbhr SnT code keliye OAT pr ruke the jabki mn bilkulbhi nhi tha. Tumhare room pr aakr takneek problem statements bnayi thi ,evaluation kiya saathme, secy ke interview liye aur ghr se coordinator ke bhi. Bachon ke liye takneek jo organize kraya tha badhiya experience tha vo. Aur haan , just a sidenote mere voh takneek ke paise abhi tk reimburse nhi huye ;). 
Now coming to SoCE. Usdin get together keliye raatbhr shrey, me, tum aur baaki Hall5 reading room me decoration, poster aur baaki cheeezen prepare ki thi. Aur badhiya tareeke se organize bhi hogya tha get together. Aur phir usidin latenight bonfire, seniors ke saath baaten kithi. Vo kaafi memorable hain. Tumhare SoCE coordi ka interview kaafi mzedar tha, "bnana h toh bnao vrna nhi" (I don't remember exactly, but aesa hi kuch similar bola tha tumne inteview me). Unfortunately, meine starting apni term ke starting mein hi society choddithi vrna aur milte hm, but 3rd yr me DesCon ke through milte rehtethe hm. 
Tumhara jaisa bnda hona chahiye kisi bhi team ya organization me, cheezon ko badi achi tareh se sambhallete ho. Kaafi ache team player ho. Aur mast bhi rehte ho aur sincere bhi ho. 
Touch me rehna, kabhi milte hain!! Best wishes for future
author: Kanishk  Chauhan

text:
Meri pyaariii roomiieee, IITK behen and my cry-mate, we only had each other even in our 1st semester (usse fights bhi boht hote the - raat ko lights ke liye, room ki safai ke liye, proper talking and living etiquette ke liye!). 1st year tera notes na dena yaad rahega mujhe üòõ. Fir apni branch same ho gyi, batti club mein saath kaam kiye. Tune boht mehanat ki thi usme aur kitni saari ppts deni padi thi na (Uff!). IME mein kaam karne mein boht maze aaye par aur voh band bas tere hi haath pe fit aata tha (kha pi liya kar kuch aur moti ho jaa, mess mein saara khana waste kar deti thi!). I will miss those long late night talks we had about so many people and topics - especially about each other‚Äôs crushes and love life üòõ! Hume ek doosre ke itne saare secrets pta na! Meko kai baar rote hue sambhala hai tune. Thanks for bearing with my repeating same talks about the same personüòÉüòÉ! Meko taekwondo mein bhi toh tu hi leke gayi thi. Paper mein mere marks dekh ke aana, mera rebate fill karna and chappal almirah mein rakhne ke liye shukriya yaar! Apne TA ke group mein bhi boht bakwas ki apan ne - maze aaye. Fir truth‚Ä¶ waali cheez! Kya kya hua hai na apne saath - ek baar toh tera fb account hi hack ho gya tha! Do you remember our 1st solo trip to oxidation pond? Tree pe chadhke photoshoot karwayeüòÅüòÅ

Yaar 4 saal were really fun and it has been great being your friend‚ù§Ô∏è. You might seem a little selfish at start but that‚Äôs not true. You are a very emotional person who cares a lot about his friends‚Äô feelings. Thanks for taking care of me all this time.

Haan yaar call pe baat nhi ki na last year. Abhi future me - we will stay connected and share a ton of secretsüòÅ!

text:
Kaha se Suru karun Yugesh aapke saath to itni memories hai. Chalo kosis karta hun.

First day of college hum sabhi Hall 5 quad me wait kar rahe the Rooms ke liye tabhi aapki entry hoti hai aur aapko dekhte hi I was like ye to poster boy hai bhai Patna ka aur phir shaam me jab room me jaata hun to dekhta hun yhi banda mera roomie bhi hai bhai literally Triple Room ka gham compensate ho gaya tha. Abhi bhi yaad hai mujhe jab mera pehla phone aaya tha to aap kitne excited the. Mafia Nights se leke Late Night Oat sessions tak bhai kitni yaadein hai. Theatre me pehli movie (Murder on the Orient express) aapne hi dikhayi thi. Wo aapka Google Pay install karwanaüòÇ. ESC101 ke exam din aapki Binary Trees ki class, TA201 exam ke liye saath me ratta maarna. Aapka hamesha motivate karte rehna. Mujpe aapka unconditional trust thanks bhai meant a lot to me. Bhai aapka facebook post jab mai Coordinator bana tha thank you yaar for your unconditional love and affection. Aapke Saath duniya daari ke debates karna. 

Ab jaldi se sum up karta hun warna 2-3 page likh dunga. Intellectual level pe to Kabhi nhi connect kar paya lekin emotional level pe hamesha connect kiya. Aapka hamesha honest suggestion dena whether ki wo accha lage ya kharab aur over the time wo hamesha hi sahi nikalte the. Hamesha aise hi suggestions dete rehna Yugesh. Aap aao na aao mai jarur aa jaunga Switzerland milne.

Bade bhai ki tarah hamesha motivate karne ke liye thanks Rommie.
